<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-09-14T10:20:48-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-09-14T10:20:48-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155276#p155276</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155276#p155276"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Porting NES Games to GBC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155276#p155276"><![CDATA[
GBA multiboot is normally used for players 2, 3, and 4 in single-pak multiplayer or for a GBA being used as a GameCube controller. It loads a program of up to about 250K into the GBA's memory. PocketNES will fit into memory so long as the game is 192K or smaller.<br /><br /><ul><li><a href="http://problemkaputt.de/gbatek.htm#biosmultibootsinglegamepak" class="postlink">GBATEK: BIOS MultiBoot</a></li><li><a href="http://problemkaputt.de/gbatek.htm#auxxboopctogbamultibootcable" class="postlink">GBATEK: GBA Xboo Cable</a></li><li><a href="http://www.devrs.com/gba/files/mbv2faqs.php" class="postlink">MBV2 FAQs</a></li><li><a href="http://axio.ms/projects/GBA/" class="postlink">8051 based multiboot cable</a></li><li><a href="http://hackaday.com/2010/03/18/arduino-based-multiboot-cable-for-game-boy-advance/" class="postlink">Arduino based multiboot cable</a></li><li><a href="http://home.mnet-online.de/al/usb_gba/usb_gba.html" class="postlink">EZ-USB (AN2131) based multiboot cable</a></li></ul><br />Is forum.gbadev.org still running?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Sep 14, 2015 10:20 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
