<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-09-14T09:35:50-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-09-14T09:35:50-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155268#p155268</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155268#p155268"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Porting NES Games to GBC]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13239&amp;p=155268#p155268"><![CDATA[
If you're willing to show the game being played in PocketNES on a GBA or GBA SP:<br /><br />Older GBA flash carts did not require an SD card; they had NOR flash memory. You could probably take the flash cart's PCB out and put it in a GBC game shell. The last such cart I remember being in production is the Fire Linker.<br /><br />Or if the NES game is 192K or smaller, you can load it through the link port using &quot;multiboot&quot;.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Sep 14, 2015 9:35 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
